{"title_page": "Valley Park School", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}}\n{{Infobox school\n| name           = Valley Park School\n| image          = Valley Park School Logo.PNG\n| image_size           = \n| coordinates    = {{coord|51.27502|0.53616|type:edu_region:GB_dim:100|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| motto          = \n| established    = \n| closed         = \n| type           = [[Academy (English school)|Academy]]\n| religious_affiliation       = \n| president      = \n| head_label     = Headteacher\n| head           = Mrs Margaret Hutchinson\n| r_head_label   = \n| r_head         = \n| chair_label    = Chair of Governors\n| chair          = Mrs Sheila Potipher\n| specialist     = [[Arts College]]\n| address         = Huntsman Lane\n| city           = [[Maidstone]]\n| county         = [[Kent]]\n| country        = [[United Kingdom]]\n| postcode       = ME14 5DT\n| local_authority            = [[Kent]]\n| ofsted         = yes\n| urn            = 136581\n| staff          = 143\n| enrolment     = 1055\n| gender         = Co-educational\n| lower_age      = 11\n| upper_age      = 18\n| colours        = Green & White\n| publication    = \n| free_1         = \n| free_label_2   = \n| free_2         = \n| free_label_3   = \n| free_3         = \n| website        = http://www.valleypark.viat.org.uk\n}}\n\n'''Valley Park School''' is an [[Academy (English school)|academy school]] in [[Maidstone]], [[Kent]], [[England]]. The school caters for girls and boys between the ages of 11 and 18.\n\nValley Park became a [[specialist school|specialist]] [[Arts College]] in July 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ofsted.gov.uk/oxedu_providers/full/(urn)/131245 |title=Valley Park Community School |publisher=Ofsted |date= |accessdate=12 June 2010}}</ref> It also has the [[Artsmark]] Gold award.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.artscouncil.org.uk/artsmark/local/media/downloads/Spreadsheet%20for%20website.xls |title=Archived copy |access-date=15 June 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110614021816/http://www.artscouncil.org.uk/artsmark/local/media/downloads/Spreadsheet%20for%20website.xls |archive-date=14 June 2011 |url-status = dead|df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nValley Park holds many activities for students e.g. focus days, trips to foreign countries and the best young farmers club in Kent. The school offers a wide range of subjects including English, Maths, History, Science, Music, P.E., Drama, D.T., I.C.T, Art, R.E., Geography, Business Studies, Modern Languages and Agriculture.\n\n==Buildings==\nOne super old building- A block \nOne new building- Taylor building \nOne terrible temporary one that could be blown away\n\n==Results==\nThe school's [[GCSE]] results are average for a secondary school, with 89% of students achieving 5 A*-C grades, with 41% 5A*-C including English and Maths.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://schools.tmg.daltonfirth.co.uk/results/ks4/2009/by/REGCODE.LEA/SE/886 |title=Telegraph.co.uk: 2009 KS4 School League Tables |publisher=Schools.tmg.daltonfirth.co.uk |date= |accessdate=12 June 2010}}</ref>\nValley Park is in the top 5% of schools nationally for [[Contextual Value Added]] with a score of 1047.9<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/shared/bsp/hi/education/09/school_tables/secondary_schools/html/886_4249.stm |title=Education &#124; League Tables &#124; Performance results for Valley Park Community School |publisher=BBC News |date=13 January 2010 |accessdate=12 June 2010}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.valleypark.kent.sch.uk Official website]\n\n{{Schools in Kent}}\n\n[[Category:Secondary schools in Kent]]\n[[Category:Academies in Kent]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}}\n{{Infobox school\n| name           = Valley Park School\n| image          = Valley Park School Logo.PNG\n| image_size           = \n| coordinates    = {{coord|51.27502|0.53616|type:edu_region:GB_dim:100|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| motto          = \n| establis